Gotv network on Saturday berthed in the confluence city of Lokoja, the Kogi State capital, amid fun and fanfare. The Regional Head, MultiChoice Nigeria, Taiwo Oguntomi, said Lokoja is the 46th city in Nigeria to have GOTV network, adding that the people of Lokoja can now enjoy over 100 channels on Gotv as other cities.   CBN’s $200b non-oil export revenue target achievable,…     E-commerce platform marks 10th anniversary with special…     Inflation increases to 17.71% – NBS   Before the event, the carnival like entrance of the service made its way to the palace of the Maigari of Lokoja, Muhammaddu Kabir Maikarfi III, who was represented by the Maiyaki of Lokoja, Alhaji Ali Lawal. Commending Gotv, a leading Digital Terrestrial Television (DTT) service provider, the monarch said: “We are glad that GOtv has come to Lokoja, and we know that GOtv will go far. This is because, from a traditional and spiritual perspective you have made the right choice by starting from the palace. When a visitor seeks royal blessings, it will not thread wrongly or derail. “I come with blessings for GOtv for recognising the royal institution. Patronising GOtv is like patronising the source of knowledge, mixed with entertainment and reports, that will widen the horizon of our thinking.’’